The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Monday, March 15, 2004 				 Steel hub retail boom
 SANJAY MANDAL																								Calcutta, March 14: A branded supermarket chain is stepping beyond the limits of the city. 																								Sniffing an industry upswing in the steel city, Durgapur, Big Bazaar, a part of Pantaloons, is moving in.																								Big Bazaar will be part of Dreamplex in the 300,000 sq ft multi-utility urban plaza, Durgapur City Centre, being set up by Bengal Shristi Infrastructure Development. The supermarket will provide a unique shopping experience for people in the region, said Hemant Kanoria, one of the promoters of the complex.																								Work on city centre, a Rs 50-crore project comprising commercial and retail plazas, a multiplex and the shopping mall, is in progress. 																								But the retail boom is not limited to one superstore. The commercial and retail plazas would house a Reliance Webstore, offices of ICICI Home Finance and HDFC Bank, Reebok and Music World outlets. There has been a turnaround in the last two or three years, said cottage and small-scale industries minister Bansagopal Chowdhury. During this period, investment worth nearly Rs 1,200 crore has been made in the iron and steel sector alone, he said.
